            <title type="main"><hi rend="i">SONGS</hi> SUNG AND RECORDED</title>
          </head>
          <p>Christopher Heppner of McGill University, Montreal, sends us the following announcement:</p>
          <p>A new work, <hi rend="i">Songs of Innocence</hi>, by David Patriquin was given its premiere on 28
March, 1984, by the St. Lawrence Choir at Christ Church Cathedral, Montreal. It consists of settings of some
of the <hi rend="i">Songs</hi> for womenâ€™s voices, harp, and flute. The work is now being recorded. Readers
interested in acquiring either the score or the recording should write to Donald Patriquin, Faculty of Music,
McGill University, 555 Sherbrooke Street West, Montreal, Quebec, Canada H3A 1E3.</p>
        </div2>
